gas and dust temperatures in the disc\nsurface is important for the line formation. We briefly discuss the effects of\nC/O ratio and choice of chemical rate network on these results. Our analysis\noffers new ways to infer the chemical and temperature structure of T Tauri\ndiscs from future JWST/MIRI observations, and to possibly detect secondary\nilluminated disc walls based on their specific mid-IR molecular signature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Jul 2018 10:47:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Jul 2018 08:35:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-17"}
